{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"Daisuke Satoh","text":"<p>Medical Doctor | Aspiring Social Epidemiologist</p>"},{"location":"#about-me","title":"About Me","text":"<p>I am a physician based in Japan, currently completing my postgraduate clinical training (2026\u20132028). My long-term goal is to pursue graduate study (MPH or PhD) in social epidemiology, with a particular focus on the social determinants of health (SDH) and health inequalities.</p>"},{"location":"#background","title":"Background","text":"<ul> <li>Education: School of Medicine, Kanazawa University</li> <li>Current role: Postgraduate clinical resident (from April 2026)</li> <li>Research interests: Social determinants of health \u00b7 Health inequalities \u00b7 Epidemiological study design \u00b7 Healthcare policy \u00b7 AI in medicine</li> </ul>"},{"location":"#learning-records","title":"Learning Records","text":"<p>I document my learning in the following areas:</p> <ul> <li>Epidemiology &amp; Biostatistics \u2014 Notes on epidemiological methods and biostatistics</li> <li>Paper Notes \u2014 Critical appraisals of research papers (epidemiology, clinical research)</li> <li>Reading notes (fiction &amp; non-fiction) \u2014 ReadEchoes</li> </ul>"},{"location":"#contact","title":"Contact","text":"<ul> <li>Email: dsatoh20@gmail.com</li> <li>GitHub</li> </ul>"},{"location":"epidemiology/","title":"\u75ab\u5b66\u30fb\u751f\u7269\u7d71\u8a08 \u30a2\u30a6\u30c8\u30d7\u30c3\u30c8","text":"<p>\u75ab\u5b66\u30fb\u751f\u7269\u7d71\u8a08\u306e\u6982\u5ff5\u7406\u89e3\u3092\u30a2\u30a6\u30c8\u30d7\u30c3\u30c8\u3059\u308b\u5834\u6240\u3002note\u8a18\u4e8b\u306e\u30c9\u30e9\u30d5\u30c8\u3092\u4e2d\u5fc3\u306b\u4fdd\u5b58\u3059\u308b\u3002</p>"},{"location":"epidemiology/#_2","title":"\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30eb\u547d\u540d\u898f\u5247","text":"<p><code>YYYY-MM-DD_\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb.md</code></p> <p>\u4f8b: <code>2026-05-10_\u4ea4\u7d61\u30